               <msContents class="#STM">
                  <summary><p><title xml:lang="ta">Ulakanīti</title> (literally "The right conduct in the world") by <persName>Ulakanātar</persName> (17th c. at the latest) is a didactic work containing aphorisms on good conduct in the form of don'ts. The present version consists in ten numbered sections of eight lines each.</p>
   <p>Description based on the examination of the original (July 2020).</p>  <p>Dimensions assessed at the time of examination.</p>      </summary>
                  
